R FOR A TOTAL OF $225,000. ONCE MORE, THE RESPONDENTS STRUCTURED A SIMILAR ARRANGEMENT WITH ANOTHER INVESTOR WHO PAID APPROXIMATELY $180,000 FOR A 5 PERCENT INTEREST IN THE INVESTMENT ADVISOR, AGAIN CONVEYED THROUGH THE RESPONDENTS' SPOUSES. THE NOMINEES DID NOT RECEIVE ANY COMPENSATION FOR THE INTERESTS THEY SURRENDERED. THE FINDINGS ALSO STATED THAT WALKER AND THE OTHER RESPONDENTS FAILED TO ACCURATELY COMPLETE ANNUAL COMPLIANCE QUESTIONNAIRES, BY CLAIMING NOT TO HAVE ANY UNDISCLOSED ACTIVITIES ON THEIR COMPLIANCE QUESTIONNAIRES, AND INACCURATELY DESCRIBED THOSE ACTIVITIES ON THEIR OUTSIDE ACTIVITY DISCLOSURE FORMS.",
